    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Here I will create some initial thoughts on how the process of setting up
an Octopress blog is, specifically when hosting it on my personal
<a href="https://dantrim.github.io">github pages website</a>.</p>

<h2 id="deploying-blog-entries-after-a-fresh-clone">Deploying Blog Entries after a Fresh Clone</h2>

<p>If you checkout your blog&#39;s repository in a new location (e.g.
a new directory or a new machine), you will first need to sync
up the <code>_deploy</code> directory with the remote&#39;s <code>master</code> branch
before running <code>rake deploy</code>. Run the following steps to achieve
this:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption> <a href='http://dantrim.github.io/downloads/code/2020-06-05/update_deploy.sh' target='_blank'>download</a></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'><span class="c">#!/bin/bash</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>git clone git@github.com:&lt;repo&gt;.git
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">cd</span> &lt;repo&gt;
</span><span class='line'>git checkout <span class="nb">source</span> <span class="c"># source is the working branch</span>
</span><span class='line'>mkdir _deploy
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">cd </span>_deploy
</span><span class='line'>git init
</span><span class='line'>git remote add origin git@github.com:&lt;repo&gt;.git
</span><span class='line'>git pull origin master <span class="c"># master is the public view of the blog</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">cd</span> ..
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

<h2 id="other-misc-changes">Other Misc Changes</h2>

<h3 id="updating-the-code-formatting-functions">Updating the code formatting functions</h3>

<p>I have found, also, that using the <code>include_code</code> blocks are apparently
the cleanest way to get code to be formatted. Though I have made
some modifications.</p>

<h3 id="removing-bulky-captions">Removing bulky captions</h3>

<p>To <code>plugins/include_code.rb</code> I have made the changes,
<figure class='code'><figcaption> <a href='http://dantrim.github.io/downloads/code/2020-06-05/include_code_snippet.rb' target='_blank'>download</a></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='rb'><span class='line'><span class="no">Dir</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">chdir</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">code_path</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">do</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">code</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">file</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="vi">@filetype</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">file</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">extname</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sub</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;.&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">if</span> <span class="vi">@filetype</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nil?</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">title</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="vi">@title</span> <span class="p">?</span> <span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="si">#{</span><span class="vi">@title</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2"> (</span><span class="si">#{</span><span class="n">file</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">basename</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2">)&quot;</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">file</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">basename</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">url</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">&quot;/</span><span class="si">#{</span><span class="n">code_dir</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2">/</span><span class="si">#{</span><span class="vi">@file</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="c1">#source = &quot;&lt;figure class=&#39;code&#39;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;span&gt;#{title}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&#39;#{url}&#39;&gt;download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;\n&quot;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">source</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">&quot;&lt;figure class=&#39;code&#39;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt; &lt;a href=&#39;</span><span class="si">#{</span><span class="n">url</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2">&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">source</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="si">#{</span><span class="no">HighlightCode</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="n">highlight</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">code</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="vi">@filetype</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2">&lt;/figure&gt;&quot;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="no">TemplateWrapper</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="n">safe_wrap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">source</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>
That is, I have replaced the original line (the commented out line in the above snippet)
with the line immediately following it.
This change removes the figure caption title and minimizes the &quot;download&quot;
tag.</p>

<h3 id="use-github-colors-for-syntax-highlighting">Use Github colors for syntax highlighting</h3>

